{
  "stem": "21786.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was standing on the famous Wenzel's Square, W-E-N-Z-E-L apostrophe S square, and cried.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We all did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And people really just looked stunned.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I discovered when I returned to my classes that two of my professors-- we call them professors-- the guy who was teaching German, his name was Janecek, J-A-N-E-C-E-K, he came to the class and had the swastika button in his lapel.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And about two weeks later, the professor who was teaching Greek-- his name was Bozka, B-O-Z-- with a hooklet K-A-- came in a SI uniform.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was one Jewish student.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It became practically untenable to do anything, so that I didn't prepare myself for German or for Greek at all.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It had no sense.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would be torn apart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I would be asked questions which had nothing to do with the subject whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My German was good, probably as good as the professor's.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I pretended that I stopped, I forgot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I saw that at the end, when there was finally the matric being written, I was left to write something which was not a matric, for I couldn't write anything in-- in Greek or in German.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was given a [INAUDIBLE] kind of pass.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For at that point, I obtained visa, student's visa, to the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I could have continued at that point at the [INAUDIBLE] High School in Bronx.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "For my aunt, who was a sister of my mother's, by the name of Rose, Rose Caplan written as a C, C-A-P-L-A-N-- sent me this paper.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Said she wanted to send the papers for the whole family, which caused the affidavit.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I could have left, but I couldn't do it on account of my parents For something happened when I was 11 years old.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
